result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th) and Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Kira Jean Mcmillan was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
1:05 p.m.  State by Special Prosecutor Chad Hendee.  Defendant present with Attorney John Smerlinski.

Attorney Hendee recites agreement - defendant will plea to count 1 - dismiss count 2.  Attorney Smerlinski concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Attorney Smerlinski indicates the defendant is waiving her right to a preliminary hearing.  Court instructs defendant of her right to a preliminary hearing.  Defendant waives this right.  Court accepts the waiver and binds the defendant over for trial.

Attorney Hendee files an Information with the court and has provided a copy to Attorney Smerlinski.  Attorney Smerlinski confirms receipt of the Information - waives reading - enters a plea of NO CONTEST on behalf of the defendant to count 1.  Court makes statement regarding the maximum penalties.  

Court goes over the plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - waived.  Court goes over the elements of the offense.  Court instructs regarding the maximum penalties.  Court instructs regarding deportation.  Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently, and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on count 1 and orders a judgment of conviction be entered today.  Court dismisses count 2.  Sentencing argument by Attorney Hendee - both counsel waive right to a Presentence Investigation - Attorney Smerlinski concurs.  Sentencing argument by Attorney Smerlinski.  No statement by the defendant.

Court orders sentence withheld and places the defendant on probation for 36 months.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
Abide with all rules/recommendations as imposed by the supervising agent.
Sentenced to 6 months county jail - with huber - commence immediately - remanded to the custody of the sheriff's department.
Pay a $600 fine plus costs.
Maintain absolute sobriety - not to possess/consume any alcohol, illegal drugs, or prescription drugs without a valid prescription.
Complete an AODA..
Not to be on any premises that is licensed to sell alcohol by-the-drink.
3 year drivers license revocation.
IID - 3 years.
Pay $28.85 blood draw costs.

Court grants sentence credit of 13 days of sentence credit if revoked.
Court orders bond on file be applied towards any fine/costs - any balance refunded to the poster.
